					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">If you did it every other frame, and had other tasks that were performed every other frame as well, you'd be able to interleave the two.</div><br />Are you saying run the game at 20-30 fps like a Micronics game?</div>
<br />No, just that <em>some</em> game tasks might be performed less-often than every frame. For example, you might have enemies do some behavior checking every other frame, or like Solomon's Key, run the enemies on a separate thread that gets whatever time is available. Definitely run movement at full speed, as 30 FPS games look sucky (Rambo for example, a sidescroller at 30 FPS, WTF?).</div>

